GARGOYLE

Gargoyles are MDC supernatural predators native to Europe's Gargoyle Empire,
which has overrun most of the continent since the Rifts.  They are massive,
winged humanoids with stone-hard MDC bodies, supernatural physical power, and
a horrific appearance that makes social interaction with other races
exceptionally difficult.  On RiftsMUD, they are not OCC eligible.

ATTRIBUTES (approximate ranges):
  IQ: 4-14   ME: 3-18   MA: 2-12   PS: 15-40 (Supernatural)
  PP: 5-20   PE: 11-36  PB: 1-6    Spd: 9-24

DAMAGE POOL:
  MDC: 3d6 x10 (approx 30-180 MDC)
  HP: PE + 2d6

SPECIAL ABILITIES:
  - MDC body: immune to SDC/HP weapons
  - Supernatural Physical Strength and Endurance
  - Natural flight (wings)
  - Nightvision 300 ft
  - Natural claws and teeth as MDC weapons

PENALTIES:
  - Not OCC eligible
  - Horrific appearance: very low MA; most beings flee or attack on sight
  - Coalition and most humanoid factions treat as kill-on-sight

OCC ELIGIBLE: No.
ALIGNMENT: Any (Gargoyle Empire tends toward Aberrant and Miscreant).

See also: gurgoyle, werewolf, races
